@startuml seq-find
'' PlantUML over Mermaid because in-page find is a strict message sequence (toggle → type → fx → paint →
'' count back) spanning re-frame and a DOM-painting module, where activations and the count-return arrow
'' matter; PlantUML sequence gives autonumber + activation + concept colour. Literal palette hexes:
'' teal #2D9574 view, blue #4F97D7 re-frame, blue-violet #7590DB app-db, green #67B11D the DOM/highlight.
!include _vv-theme.iuml

title In-page find — Ctrl+F ⟶ highlighted matches (CSS Custom Highlight API)

autonumber "<b>[0]"

actor User #9F8766
participant "find-bar /\nkeybindings" as UI #2D9574
participant "re-frame\nevents" as RF #4F97D7
collections "app-db\n:ui/find" as DB #7590DB
participant "re-frame\nfx" as FX #4F97D7
participant "finder\n(renderer.find)" as F #67B11D
participant "CSS.highlights\n+ DOM Ranges" as H #67B11D

== open the find bar ==
User -> UI : Ctrl+F
UI -> RF : [:find/toggle]
activate RF
RF -> DB : assoc :ui/find :visible? true
deactivate RF
DB --> UI : :ui/find sub → render <input auto-focus>

== type a query ==
User -> UI : type "needle"
UI -> RF : [:find/set-query "needle"]
activate RF
RF -> DB : assoc :ui/find :query "needle"
RF -> FX : fx **:find/run "needle"**
deactivate RF
activate FX
FX -> F : **finder/search! "needle"**
activate F
F -> F : collect-ranges:\nTreeWalker(SHOW_TEXT) over .vv-content\ncase-insensitive indexOf in each text node
F -> H : Highlight.add(range) ∀ matches\nCSS.highlights.set "vv-find" / "vv-find-current"
F -> H : scrollIntoView {block:center} first match
F --> FX : return count = n
deactivate F
FX -> RF : rf/dispatch [:find/count n]
deactivate FX
activate RF
RF -> DB : :ui/find :count n, :idx (if n>0 then 1 else 0)
deactivate RF
DB --> UI : render "idx/n"

== cycle matches ==
User -> UI : Enter (Shift+Enter = prev)
UI -> RF : [:find/cycle +1]  (or -1)
RF -> FX : fx :find/cycle dir
activate FX
FX -> F : **finder/cycle! dir**
activate F
F -> F : idx ≔ (idx + dir) mod n
F -> H : repaint "vv-find-current"\n+ scrollIntoView
F --> FX : return (inc idx)  [1-based]
deactivate F
FX -> RF : [:find/idx i]
deactivate FX
RF -> DB : assoc :ui/find :idx i

== close ==
User -> UI : Escape
UI -> RF : [:find/close]
RF -> DB : :visible? false
RF -> FX : fx :find/clear → finder/clear!\n(delete both highlights)

note over F, H #FFF6D6
  No DOM mutation: matches are painted as live Ranges via the
  CSS Custom Highlight API, styled by ::highlight(vv-find) /
  ::highlight(vv-find-current). If unsupported (supported? = false)
  find degrades to no-op — the document is never altered.
end note

legend right
  |= Colour |= Participant / concept |
  |<#9F8766>| User |
  |<#2D9574>| view (find-bar, keybindings) |
  |<#4F97D7>| re-frame events + effects |
  |<#7590DB>| app-db :ui/find slice |
  |<#67B11D>| finder + CSS.highlights painting (DOM) |
endlegend
@enduml
